    <string name="acknowledgements"><b>StudyBuddy v1.0</b>\n
<b>Created By:</b>\n
James Hollowell &lt;jthollo@clemson.edu&gt;\n
Created for the Spring 2017 section of CPSC 4820\n\n
<b>Information</b>\n\n
This application is designed to keep an inventory of vehicles\' basic information, with plans for expansion in the future.\n
 - To add a vehicle, tap the add button.\n
 - To edit a vehicle, tap it\'s entry in the list, and toggle edit mode in the top right corner.\n
 - To reorder the list, simply long press and drag the vehicle, or tap and drag the handle on the vehicle.\n
 - To delete a vehicle, swipe it off the list. This sends it to the trashcan, where you can later restore it.\n\n
When using either the add or edit activities, the save button only appears when changes occur. Additionally, making changes forces the cancel button to require additional confirmation.\n\n

<b>What\'s new</b>\n\n
This application uses Android\'s DataBinding library to simplify some code with the UI. It also uses a SQLite database to store the information. The design should also allow for rotation by utilizing the scrolling. Finally, the app implements gestures for interacting with the RecyclerView.\n
This application also uses an external database and external web application to facilitate users moving between a web and multiple phones.\n\n

